have in common with Jimmy.

42:05.974 --> 42:07.724
Because we were comin' out of punk rock.

42:07.725 --> 42:11.516
And punk rock was not
about shiny things.

42:11.517 --> 42:14.807
Actually, it was about
defacing shiny things.

42:14.808 --> 42:18.265
And Jimmy was a bit slick for us.

42:18.266 --> 42:20.848
But he... he happens to you.

42:20.849 --> 42:22.807
He's like a virus...

42:22.808 --> 42:26.932
that enters the system uninvited,

42:26.933 --> 42:28.932
takes over all your main organs,

42:28.933 --> 42:30.057
gets to the brain.

42:30.058 --> 42:31.724
It's like, he knows

42:31.725 --> 42:34.599
this is going to work out
well for both of you.

42:34.600 --> 42:36.848
I didn't.

42:42.475 --> 42:44.432
♪ Yeah, give it up ♪

42:44.433 --> 42:47.350
♪ Sunday, Bloody Sunday ♪

42:48.683 --> 42:52.016
♪ Sunday, Bloody Sunday ♪

43:02.725 --> 43:05.557
And then Jimmy just
chased us around the world

43:05.558 --> 43:07.599
until we agreed to go
into the studio with him.

43:07.600 --> 43:09.682
He would not take no for an answer.

43:09.683 --> 43:13.307
So we did Under a Blood Red Sky.
It was a live album.

43:13.308 --> 43:16.516
And we went to New York
to do the mixing.

43:16.517 --> 43:17.932
And he showed us around New York.

43:17.933 --> 43:19.641
And that's where we really understood

43:19.642 --> 43:21.848
the Italian aspect of him...

43:21.849 --> 43:23.390
the family, the food.

43:23.391 --> 43:25.973
You know, that's when
we realized that really

43:25.974 --> 43:27.682
Irish people are Italians.

43:27.683 --> 43:29.182
It's just we don't eat as well,

43:29.183 --> 43:32.390
we don't dress as well,
we don't play soccer as well.

43:32.391 --> 43:33.766
But we can sing.

