46:02.350 --> 46:04.682
♪ Start runnin' for the door
but the fucker never made it ♪

46:04.683 --> 46:06.307
♪ The sound of the nine went bang! ♪

46:06.308 --> 46:09.890
It was just the beginnin'
of us makin' some real money,

46:09.891 --> 46:12.349
after years of nickels and dimes.

46:12.350 --> 46:16.265
Now we'd be able to buy houses, cars.

46:16.266 --> 46:17.641
Rich.

46:17.642 --> 46:19.599
That was the first
time we ever had contracts.

46:19.600 --> 46:21.557
But Cube wanted somebody
to look at the paperwork.

46:21.558 --> 46:23.057
I still got me a little Jeep.

46:23.058 --> 46:24.557
I'm at my mother house.

46:24.558 --> 46:26.682
Now, this is when the trouble started.

46:26.683 --> 46:28.390
Ice Cube left in a bitter dispute.

46:32.266 --> 46:33.973
I don't like the manager,

46:33.974 --> 46:35.890
'cause he wasn't payin' me my money.

46:35.891 --> 46:37.724
That's the bottom line. Bottom line.

46:37.725 --> 46:40.307
That's it. No more N.W.A.

46:40.308 --> 46:42.683
No more N.W.A. questions, please.

46:44.225 --> 46:45.557
You're gonna leave?

46:50.266 --> 46:52.224
I got Cube on the phone.

46:52.225 --> 46:53.641
He felt he was gettin' fucked,

46:53.642 --> 46:55.932
and Jerry was the reason for it,

46:55.933 --> 46:58.015
and Eazy was condonin' it.

46:58.016 --> 46:59.307
He was talkin' to me about,

46:59.308 --> 47:02.015
"Dre, you gotta take a look
at your financials, dude."

47:02.016 --> 47:04.307
And then Suge Knight
enters the building.

47:04.308 --> 47:06.432
D.O.C. introduced me to him.

47:06.433 --> 47:07.932
Suge was my guy.

47:07.933 --> 47:10.349
Big-ass dude. Super friendly.

47:10.350 --> 47:14.182
And Suge says, "Let me take you
to this guy. He can help us out."

47:14.183 --> 47:16.098
So Suge took my contracts

47:16.099 --> 47:18.432
to a guy named Dick Griffey.

47:18.433 --> 47:19.599
He started tellin' me

47:19.600 --> 47:21.390
I should be getting
this amount of money,

47:21.391 --> 47:23.432
and this amount of points
for each record.

47:23.433 --> 47:24.973
And you're only getting this.

47:24.974 --> 47:26.724
So I'm, like, "Okay."

47:26.725 --> 47:29.682
Went back to the studio not knowin'

47:29.683 --> 47:32.848
if Eazy knows about this shit or not.

47:32.849 --> 47:35.015
And Eazy is just goin' crazy.

47:35.016 --> 47:37.182
"Fuck Cube this, fuck Cube that."

47:37.183 --> 47:38.641
Somebody start shootin'.

47:38.642 --> 47:40.807
Up until then,
everything that we had done

47:40.808 --> 47:42.848
was like the ultimate brotherhood,

47:42.849 --> 47:44.807
at least, from my perspective.

47:44.808 --> 47:48.307
And all of a sudden,
it just turned into business,

47:48.308 --> 47:50.098
and it turned into pressure.

47:50.099 --> 47:51.807
You know, there was
a lot of distractions,

47:51.808 --> 47:54.516
but to me, Dre had always
seemed driven in the studio.

47:54.517 --> 47:57.474
Had people comin' in
playing bass and instruments,

47:57.475 --> 47:59.599
and so it was a lot more funk to it.

47:59.600 --> 48:01.641
I'm tryin' to prove
myself as an engineer,

48:01.642 --> 48:05.224
as an artist, as a
producer without Cube.

48:05.225 --> 48:08.724
For me, it all became
just a point to make.

48:08.725 --> 48:12.349
Cube was, I'd like to say,
the spirit of N.W.A.

48:12.350 --> 48:17.015
His anti-establishment feel
drove that early sound.

48:17.016 --> 48:18.932
And Cube's our lead guy.

48:18.933 --> 48:20.265
He's gone, so I'm hearin'

48:20.266 --> 48:21.848
different shit around the streets.

48:21.849 --> 48:24.641
"N.W.A. is nothin'. They're gone."

48:24.642 --> 48:26.516
That started touchin'
my ego a little bit.

48:26.517 --> 48:29.224
Find out what's
goin' on on my new solo project.

48:29.225 --> 48:30.349
"AmeriKKKa's Most Wanted."

48:30.350 --> 48:32.682
Ah, Cube in y'all ass, man.

48:32.683 --> 48:34.474
What the fuck y'all gonna do?

48:38.808 --> 48:41.140
Pump It Up was a nationally

48:41.141 --> 48:44.057
syndicated music video show.

48:44.058 --> 48:46.015
I was a fan of the music,

48:46.016 --> 48:48.182
so I wanted to present
that to other fans.

48:48.183 --> 48:49.682
Let's see if success and money

48:49.683 --> 48:52.057
has changed the meanest men in rap.

48:52.058 --> 48:53.890
They agreed to do this interview for me,

48:53.891 --> 48:56.057
'cause it was Dee, their home girl.

48:56.058 --> 48:58.557
And the interview
I wound up doin' with N.W.A....

48:58.558 --> 48:59.807
awkward.

48:59.808 --> 49:03.848
Excuse me. Hi. Is Eazy-E here, N.W.A.?

49:03.849 --> 49:05.973
Hey, what's up, you guys? Come here.

49:05.974 --> 49:07.265
- What's up?
- What's up?

49:07.266 --> 49:09.307
Everybody knows this is Eazy-E.

49:09.308 --> 49:10.557
- Yo!
- Dr. Dre.

49:10.558 --> 49:14.265
From the very moment it started,

49:14.266 --> 49:15.973
the energy was bad.

49:15.974 --> 49:17.057
Wow, it's too quiet.

49:17.058 --> 49:18.557
Y'all gotta wake up. Come on, y'all.

49:18.558 --> 49:20.182
It seemed like with every question,

49:20.183 --> 49:23.766
they found a way
to get verbal jabs at Cube.

49:23.767 --> 49:25.641
Do you guys still
communicate with him or...

49:25.642 --> 49:26.807
- Nah.
- Only time we communicate

49:26.808 --> 49:28.474
is when they have
little run-ins, you know.

49:28.475 --> 49:29.766
So the interview's done,

49:29.767 --> 49:31.390
and it hadn't aired yet.

49:31.391 --> 49:34.890
Next thing I know, my producer
wanted to film Ice Cube's rebuttal

49:34.891 --> 49:37.724
and put it in the show with N.W.A.

49:37.725 --> 49:40.848
Personal beef. Let's... let's
milk this for what it is.

49:40.849 --> 49:42.432
This is Ice Cube on Pump It Up.

49:42.433 --> 49:45.015
I got all suckers 100 miles and running.

49:45.016 --> 49:47.474
Like to give a shout out to the D.O.C.

49:47.475 --> 49:48.599
Y'all can't play me.

49:48.600 --> 49:50.932
That was their mentality,
sensationalism.

49:50.933 --> 49:53.265
Sista Dee, always
in the middle of controversy

49:53.266 --> 49:54.641
right here on Pump It Up.

49:54.642 --> 49:59.098
I was 22 at the time. I'm not Oprah.

49:59.099 --> 50:01.057
I didn't know that there's still more

50:01.058 --> 50:02.724
internal struggles in the group.

50:02.725 --> 50:04.057
Not even after Cube left.

50:04.058 --> 50:06.098
I just figured, "Okay, ego."

50:06.099 --> 50:08.432
But out of four remaining, I was like,

50:08.433 --> 50:10.599
"Hmm. Whose ego is gonna be next?"

50:10.600 --> 50:13.265
The ego was a motherfucker.

50:13.266 --> 50:15.766
It's almost like the little pilot light

50:15.767 --> 50:17.766
and fame is the gasoline.

50:17.767 --> 50:19.848
And once gasoline
gets poured on that ego,

50:19.849 --> 50:23.390
you never know if the pilot
light is gonna go out

50:23.391 --> 50:26.015
or if it's gonna turn
into a motherfuckin' bonfire

50:26.016 --> 50:28.642
or some shit that nobody could control.

50:31.642 --> 50:34.641
I remember, uh, us bein' in the studio

50:34.642 --> 50:38.265
and Dre was tryin' to talk
to E about the money.

50:38.266 --> 50:40.724
And E would always be,
like, "Talk to Jerry."

50:40.725 --> 50:42.506
And Dre don't want to talk to Jerry.

50:42.531 --> 50:43.671
I said, "Listen man.

50:43.696 --> 50:46.140
"Fuck all of this goin' back
and forth shit, man.

50:46.141 --> 50:48.432
Either Jerry goes or I go."

50:48.433 --> 50:49.848
And he looked me in my face and said,

50:49.849 --> 50:51.642
"I can't get rid of Jerry."

50:53.558 --> 50:57.183
That was the end of me
and Eazy-E's relationship.

50:58.974 --> 51:02.307
He had to really trust
Jerry to get rid of Dre.

51:02.308 --> 51:05.016
'Cause Dre was the main ingredient.

51:06.225 --> 51:08.517
The feelin' I had at that moment...

51:11.350 --> 51:13.517
was, um...

51:16.391 --> 51:19.516
similar to losin' a brother.

51:19.517 --> 51:21.432
Seriously broke my heart.

51:21.433 --> 51:24.766
All I remember is
walkin' out of the studio

51:24.767 --> 51:27.599
and everything just bein' a blur.

51:27.600 --> 51:31.098
Like a slow motion walk to that car.

51:31.099 --> 51:33.516
There was so many things goin' on

51:33.517 --> 51:35.390
and all the loss.

51:35.391 --> 51:37.432
It was a terrible space
for me at the time.

51:37.433 --> 51:40.182
And I guess, you know...

51:40.183 --> 51:41.973
a lot of people have
their ways of dealin'

51:41.974 --> 51:43.641
with things of that nature.

51:43.642 --> 51:45.391
I turned to alcohol.

51:47.642 --> 51:50.015
So it was the night
before the American Music Awards.

51:50.016 --> 51:52.766
And, um, it was a Def Jam party.

51:52.767 --> 51:55.557
I spotted Dre. He was drunk.

51:55.558 --> 51:57.265
And I think he looked my way,

51:57.266 --> 51:59.057
but he didn't smile.

51:59.058 --> 52:02.265
And it looked like he wasn't
gonna speak to me at all.

52:02.266 --> 52:04.307
And the next thing I know,
he snatched me up.

52:04.308 --> 52:06.057
When I say he snatched me up,

52:06.058 --> 52:07.516
my feet were off the ground.

52:07.517 --> 52:08.682
It was like, "Shit."

52:08.683 --> 52:11.098
You know, like the strength...

52:11.099 --> 52:13.015
and the rage.

52:13.016 --> 52:15.390
And, uh, you know.

52:15.391 --> 52:17.807
Everybody knows the story from there.

52:17.808 --> 52:19.641
In Los Angeles, Dee Barnes,

52:19.642 --> 52:22.224
host of the Fox TV rap show Pump It Up,

52:22.225 --> 52:24.516
is filing a civil suit against Dr. Dre

52:24.517 --> 52:27.432
and claims that
last January at an LA club,

52:27.433 --> 52:28.599
Dre assaulted her,

52:28.600 --> 52:29.724
grabbing her hair,

52:29.725 --> 52:31.682
slamming her face and body into a wall,

52:31.683 --> 52:33.474
and kicking her in the ribs.

52:33.475 --> 52:35.932
Barnes' attorneys say
that Dre was apparently upset

52:35.933 --> 52:38.724
that one of Barnes' producers
inserted her interview

52:38.725 --> 52:40.890
with ex-N.W.A. member Ice Cube

52:40.891 --> 52:44.265
into a Pump It Up show
last winter featuring N.W.A.

52:44.266 --> 52:47.182
N.W.A.'s independent
publicist says, quote,

52:47.183 --> 52:49.265
"I know Dr. Dre as a gentle soul,

52:49.266 --> 52:51.390
the loving father of a baby boy."

52:51.391 --> 52:54.057
I don't think I was
out of touch with reality,

52:54.058 --> 52:55.932
but I was Dr. Dre,

52:55.933 --> 52:59.848
and this was, uh, a very
low point in my life.

52:59.849 --> 53:01.682
And, um...

53:01.683 --> 53:05.848
I've done a lot of
stupid shit in my life,

53:05.849 --> 53:09.140
a lot of things that I wish
I could go and take back.

53:12.808 --> 53:14.265
I've experienced abuse.

53:14.266 --> 53:17.224
I've, um, watched my mother

53:17.225 --> 53:19.307
get abused, you know?

53:19.308 --> 53:20.474
So, it's like,

53:20.475 --> 53:23.307
there's absolutely no excuse for it.

53:23.308 --> 53:26.057
No woman should ever
be treated that way.

53:26.058 --> 53:29.057
Any man that puts his hands on a female

53:29.058 --> 53:30.557
is a fuckin' idiot.

53:30.558 --> 53:32.307
He's out of his fuckin' mind,

53:32.308 --> 53:36.307
and I was out of my
fuckin' mind at the time.

53:36.308 --> 53:37.641
I fucked up.

53:37.642 --> 53:39.848
I paid for it. I'm sorry for it.

53:39.849 --> 53:41.808
And I apologized for it.

53:44.517 --> 53:46.973
I have this dark cloud that follows me,

53:46.974 --> 53:49.973
and it's gonna be
attached to me forever.

53:49.974 --> 53:54.516
It's a major blemish
on who I am as a man.

53:54.517 --> 53:56.057
And every time it comes up,

53:56.058 --> 53:58.182
it just makes me feel fucked up.

53:58.183 --> 54:00.682
So it's just like, what do I do?

54:00.683 --> 54:02.848
What do I do to get rid
of this dark cloud?

54:02.849 --> 54:05.516
I don't know what else to do.

54:05.517 --> 54:07.474
I'm learnin'.

54:07.475 --> 54:09.182
I'm tryin' to become a better person,

54:09.183 --> 54:10.475
become a better man.

54:12.350 --> 54:15.015
From... from a personal standpoint,

54:15.016 --> 54:19.015
I feel like I've handled it well.

54:19.016 --> 54:21.015
I had to stand up

54:21.016 --> 54:22.140
just because I would probably

54:22.141 --> 54:24.224
never forgive myself if I didn't.

54:24.225 --> 54:25.474
Dee Barnes' civil suit

54:25.475 --> 54:27.057
charges him with assault and battery,

54:27.058 --> 54:29.682
inflicting emotional distress,
and defamation.

54:29.683 --> 54:33.474
Barnes seeks damages over $10 million.

54:33.475 --> 54:37.099
I called the police
on Mr. Fuck Tha Police.

54:38.808 --> 54:40.932
But little by little,

54:40.933 --> 54:43.224
the work started dryin' up.

54:43.225 --> 54:46.265
It was as if I had ruined his career

54:46.266 --> 54:49.683
by being that disturbing
footnote in his legacy.

54:51.266 --> 54:53.224
But, um, I went through the...

54:53.225 --> 54:55.807
the anger and the, uh, the dismay,

54:55.808 --> 54:58.766
and you know, I worked...
I worked those things out,

54:58.767 --> 55:01.516
um, to where... to where
I got to a place of peace.

55:01.517 --> 55:03.182
Forgiveness is about...

55:03.183 --> 55:05.015
It's not really about the other person.

55:05.016 --> 55:07.224
Forgiveness is about... for you.

55:07.225 --> 55:08.432
You do it for yourself,

55:08.433 --> 55:10.266
because what are you
gonna do with all that anger?

55:14.266 --> 55:15.391
Hmm.

55:17.099 --> 55:18.890
In the end,

55:18.891 --> 55:20.599
I've hurt people that I care about,

55:20.600 --> 55:23.391
and for that, I'm really sorry.

55:27.266 --> 55:28.641
In 1984,

55:28.642 --> 55:31.766
I went with my father
to his father's funeral.

55:31.767 --> 55:33.224
And the next morning,

55:33.225 --> 55:35.599
I went back to LA and I get
a phone call from my sister

55:35.600 --> 55:37.599
that my dad had a heart attack.

55:37.600 --> 55:39.599
So I rushed back to New York,

55:39.600 --> 55:42.265
and about six weeks later,

55:42.266 --> 55:43.891
his mother died.

55:45.058 --> 55:46.682
